hout the Scutum arm.\nThe n(e) derived from [N II] for these molecular cloud regions are about 30\ncm{-3}, and probably arise in the ionized boundary layers of clouds. This [N\nII] emission from the ionized boundary layers is probably the result of the\nshock compression of the WIM as it impacts the arm's neutral gas, but some\ncould arise from extended HII regions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 7 Aug 2017 21:19:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-11-29"}
